title: For Trade:  Gap letter IHC International Harvester M1 Garand
location: Dupage County IL, Illinois, United States
postcontent: What I have listed here is a CMP documented Gap letter IHC M1 Garand. International Harvester Garands accounted for approximately 7% of total Garand production. They had three different receiver types, postage stamp, gap letter, and arrowhead. In rarity the IHC Garands are king. Gap letter IHC's being the second rarest variant only to arrowheads. This one being offered is very nice! It went through Rock Island Armory at some point as evident by the RIA stamp on the stock. It was also re parkerised while there. The surprising part is it retained several of its IHC parts, as well as the IHC stock! The Opp rod is a WWII cut SA, and the gas plug is a make I am unfamiliar with. It retained it's original LMR barrel from 53 with the ordanences wheel stamp, not the DOD stamp. The stock indicates it was a later production 52 via the barrel channel numbers. This rifle would make a true gem in any collection. Please request more pictures, I have several to send. As of Tuesday, I listed this gun on Gunbroker. I figured I would see what was out there in trade before the reserve is hit. Let's see what you have.

title: For Sale:  SIG 290RS Extreme
location: Raleigh, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent: I am looking to sell my Sig 290RS (Re-Strike), this Re-Strike capability is to allow the shooter to continuously pull the trigger on the 290RS if for some reason the round did not fire the first time. With just about every other semi auto handgun this would be classified as a malfunction and you would have to rack the slide which in turn would extract the unfired round and reset the trigger. But not the 290RS, it will allow you to continuously pull the trigger until that round is fired. I bought this for my wife because she would not have to clear such a malfunction and could keep pulling the trigger. She has now decided that she would rather have a .380. She has fired 12 rounds through it. It comes with box and papers, and one magazine. You can tell from the pictures it has not been used hardly at all. title: For Sale:  Solvent Trap - 10 Pre-formed & Center Marked Freeze Plugs - Fit Maglite D Cell
postcontent:
A full set of 10 freeze plugs (1.35" / 34.3mm) pre-formed & center marked with precision. The perfect compliment to your maglite solvent trap project, or approved form 1 build. These are completely legal, as long as you do not drill through them before receiving approval for your form 1 build and tax stamp from the BATF.

These steel freeze plugs are formed on a 20-ton press to maintain a complete forming, and a consistent shape. These have concentric cones, with a consistent angle and the center point clearly marked for easier installation. The cone is formed at roughly a 50 degree angle to the perpendicular center line of the walls.

I also offer center marked (not formed) freeze plugs.

I do not sell the C-Cell plugs, or recommend that size. It has a dramatically reduced internal volume, which reduces it's usefulness. Also, the plugs being used for the C-cell are flared out to fit. This means that only the outermost point of the plug is making contact with the wall, and leaves it prone to turning out of position if exposed to pressure. In my experience, you'll be much further ahead, and safer, if you use the D-cell instead.

I will not ship outside of US.

title: For Sale:  Type 38 School Arisaka
postcontent:
This is a Type 38 Arisaka. This one is different than your average Type 38 though! If you look above the 3 Kanji on the receiver (between the mum and the three lines), that symbol means that this was a school Arisaka! There is some damage to the front part of the top handguard as you can see in the picture. The ring of "o"s around the mum means it was also taken out of Imperial Army service which is further proof that this is indeed a Type 38 School Arisaka.
To add to this special find, it DOES include the dust cover and a bayonet! A great piece for any Japanese collection!

title: For Sale:  Glock 30 .45 ACP Excellent condition.  Great Protection Piece!
postcontent:
Per Glock;  "The GLOCK 30 in the legendary .45 AUTO offers excellent out-of-the-box precision paired with the ballistic quality of this genuine big-bore caliber. Its compact design and simple operation allow smooth drawing in a .45 caliber pistol. With all of these advantages, especially because of its compact dimensions, the G30 is the first choice of plainclothes officers and security personnel in the US."

I have owned this pistol for several years and it has been my primary protection piece hidden away inside my vehicle.  I've taken this pistol to the range at least once every 6 months and have fired a box of shells through it to be sure everything was up to having my life depend on it.  I can honestly say that with any brand of factory .45 ACP ammo that I've never had even one single failure of any kind.  Even better, this pistol is as accurate as some of my .45's that I have 4X or 5X as much money invested in.

The sights are TruGlo fiber optic sights (not TFO) that convinced me to go with a different color front sight.  I always thought it looked dumb to have a different color front sight, but I can draw this weapon and fire on target much faster than I can with any weapon with matching sights.  I hate to see my baby go, but I can no longer justify having 2 or 3 of the same pistols sitting around.  Depending on how much you want to spend, I have tons of extra magazines I could add to this pistol.  

It comes with 2 along with the original paperwork, cleaning brush etc. that came with the pistol.  Sitting right next to me I see 4 additional 10 round factory Glock mags, each with the $6 Pierce pinky extension (as pictured with the 2 in the box) as well as 3 of the factory Glock 13 round magazines.  The buyer has the option to buy the 10 rounders with Pierce pinky extensions for $12 each and/or the 13 round factory Glock .45 ACP magazines for $17 each.  Heck, I even found to brand new 28 round .45 ACP mags that I'll let go for $20 to the buyer of the pistol.  You can REALLY be locked and loaded when leaving the house if you buy all the mags with the pistol!!

For a quick sale, the Glock 30 with box, papers and original 2 mags for $449.  You can add to that whatever additional magazines you want.  Buyer must have valid IN driver's license and preferably an IN carry permit.

postcontent:
I have two (2) (dos, zwei) vintage ammo containers for sale.  Both are in decent condition with some surface rust.  I left them un-restored to allow collector's to keep the patina or customizers to seal and paint them as they wish.

Great for ammo storage, home decor, prepping, or whatever fetish you people are in to.  Hurry up and grab this memoir of the Greatest Generation before the socialists take it away and redistribute it!
